==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|know}} + {{term|it}} + {{term|all}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[know]]-[[it]]-[[all]]}}

# One given to pontificating as if they know everything and behave as if they're above others, normally intended as a [[pejorative]].
#: ''We were all proposing ideas to solve the problem until some '''know-it-all''' strutted in the room telling us how our ideas wouldn't work and what actually needed to be done.''

